'''Evgeny Pigusov''' ({{lang-ru|<U+0415><U+0432><U+0433><U+0435><U+043D><U+0438><U+0439> <U+041F><U+0438><U+0433><U+0443><U+0441><U+043E><U+0432>}}; born March 31, 1961 in [[Kemerovo]]) is a [[Russia]]n [[chess]] [[Grandmaster (chess)|Grandmaster]] (1987). He took part in the [[FIDE World Chess Championship 2002]], but was knocked out in the third round by [[Alexey Dreev]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mark-weeks.com/chess/a1a2$wix.htm|title=World Chess Championship  2001-02 FIDE Knockout Matches|publisher=Mark-Weeks.com|accessdate=2 January 2012}}</ref>

He played in the [[Soviet Union]] Junior Chess Championships of 1977.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://al20102007.narod.ru/ch_urs/1977/ch_jun77.html|title=USSR Junior Chess Championship, Riga, 1977|publisher=RusBase|accessdate=2 January 2012}}</ref> He tied for 1st at Havana 1986 and Sochi 1987, tied for 2nd at Moscow 1987 and Dordrecht 1988.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chessgames.com/player/evgeny_pigusov.html|title=The chess games of Evgeny Pigusov|publisher=ChessGames.com|accessdate=2 January 2012}}</ref> In 1989 he tied for 8th<U+2013>10th with [[Alexander Chernin]] and [[Alexey Vyzmanavin]] in the GMA's Open in Moscow.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://al20102007.narod.ru/it/1989/moscup89.html|title=GMA-Open Moscow 16-25.5.1989|publisher=RusBase|accessdate=2 January 2012}}</ref>

